data.text:
As a junior, 2008: Did not play due to elbow injury sustained in preseason.

As a sophomore, 2007: Earned 41 starts and played in 45 games after beginning season injured ... was a monster in first game back, going 2-for-4 with a home run, RBI and two runs scored against Towson (2/25) ... put together a nine-game hitting streak that lasted from March 4-17 ... began streak with career-best 3-for-3 performance against Florida A&M (3/4) ... set new career-high with three RBIs against Georgia Southern (4/10) ... tied career-best with three RBIs against Ohio State after knocking out three-run blast (5/15) ... went 2-for-6 and scored twice in UNF's 15-8 upset win over Florida (5/8) ... tied career-high with three hits against Kennesaw State (4/14) ... finished second on team with eight stolen bases ... tied for second on team with four sacrifice bunts ... tallied game-winning RBI in UNF's final win of season against Gardner-Webb (5/19).

As a redshirt freshman, 2006: Played in 21 games and started six... batted .292 (7-for-24) with 11 runs scored ... went 2-for-4 with two runs scored and an RBI against ETSU on March 19... tallied two doubles and three walks... finished with a .990 fielding percentage ...recorded eight putouts and one assist.

As a freshman, 2005: Redshirted.

High School: 2004 graduate of Bishop Kenny High School, where he played for Bob West ... batted .380 as a junior ... raised his average to .410 as a senior en route to earning team MVP honors ... garnered all-city honors as a senior ... also lettered in basketball, earning Defensive Player of the Year honors as a senior.

Personal: Majoring in building construction ... born June 19, 1986, in Tupelo, Miss. ... hometown is Fernandina Beach, Fla. ... son of Billy and Lindsay Burbank and Michael Wilson ... lists barbecue as his favorite food and the late Pat Tillman as his favorite sports personality.
